    <stitle>FRAME - FIFTH WHEEL INSTALLATION - MAINTENANCE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="0">
        <title>MAINTENANCE</title>
        <para>The fifth wheel should be properly maintained to ensure proper operation. The following is a general
            guideline for maintaining the fifth wheel.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Always keep the track of sliding fifth wheels as clean as possible.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Periodically lubricate all moving parts of fixed and sliding fifth wheels.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect fifth wheel for proper operation.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Inspect fifth wheel for damaged or missing parts. Replace as required.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Be sure all bolts retaining fifth wheel assembly to vehicle frame are properly tightened.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
